import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy — Rally Trivia" description="Rally Trivia's privacy policy covering our mobile apps, web platform, and marketing website.">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="py-32 md:py-40 bg-surface-blue px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-heading leading-tight mb-6">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>
      <p class="text-body">
        <strong>Effective Date:</strong> February 23, 2026 &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Last Updated:</strong> February 23, 2026
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Policy Content -->
  <section class="py-24 px-4 bg-white">
    <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-slate prose-lg prose-headings:text-heading prose-a:text-primary prose-a:decoration-primary/30 hover:prose-a:decoration-primary prose-hr:border-border">

      <p>
        Rally Trivia ("Rally Trivia," "we," "our," or "us") provides a live trivia management platform and related marketing website.
      </p>
      <p>This Privacy Policy applies to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>The Rally Trivia mobile applications (iOS and Android)</li>
        <li>The Rally Trivia web application platform</li>
        <li>The marketing website located at <a href="https://www.rallytrivia.com">https://www.rallytrivia.com</a></li>
        <li>Any related services or event experiences</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, how we share it, and your rights.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2>1. Overview of Data Practices</h2>
      <p>Rally Trivia is designed to operate without collecting personally identifiable information from event participants.</p>
      <p>The mobile app:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Does not require name or email registration</li>
        <li>Does not create persistent personal accounts</li>
        <li>Uses event access codes and team PINs that are not tied to a real-world identity</li>
        <li>Does not display advertising</li>
        <li>Does not use cross-app tracking</li>
        <li>Does not sell personal information</li>
      </ul>

      <hr />

      <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>We collect limited categories of data necessary to operate and improve the service.</p>

      <h3>A. Event Access Credentials</h3>
      <p>The app uses event access codes and team PIN codes. These credentials are session-based, are not tied to personal identities, and are not linked to names, emails, or other personal information.</p>

      <h3>B. Identifiers</h3>
      <p>We may automatically collect technical identifiers such as:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>IP address</li>
        <li>Device type and operating system</li>
        <li>App version</li>
        <li>General geographic region (city/state level)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>These identifiers are used for security, performance monitoring, and service reliability.</p>

      <h3>C. Usage Data (Product Interaction)</h3>
      <p>We collect interaction data such as feature usage, session activity, screen transitions, and error events. This data is used only for analytics, app functionality, and product improvement.</p>
      <p>Product interaction data is <strong>not linked to a user's identity</strong>.</p>

      <h3>D. Crash Data &amp; Diagnostics</h3>
      <p>We use <strong>Microsoft Azure Application Insights</strong> for crash reporting, error logging, performance monitoring, and service availability monitoring.</p>
      <p>Crash and diagnostic data may include error messages, stack traces, performance metrics, and device characteristics. This information is used strictly for app functionality, stability improvements, analytics, and security.</p>
      <p>Diagnostic data is <strong>not used for advertising</strong> and is <strong>not linked to a personal identity</strong>.</p>

      <h3>E. Marketing Website Analytics</h3>
      <p><strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> — Google Analytics may collect IP address, device and browser information, page views, and referrer data. This is used to understand website performance and marketing effectiveness. Learn more at <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google's partner sites policy</a>.</p>
      <p><strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> — Cloudflare Web Analytics does not use cookies, does not track users across websites, and collects only aggregated, anonymized traffic metrics.</p>
      <p>Website analytics do not affect the mobile app.</p>

      <h3>F. Contact Form Submissions (Website Only)</h3>
      <p>If you submit a demo request on our website, we may collect your name, email address, organization name, and event information. This data is used solely to respond to your inquiry.</p>
      <p>The mobile app itself does not collect names or email addresses.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2>3. Tracking &amp; Advertising</h2>
      <p>Rally Trivia does <strong>not</strong>:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Track users across third-party apps or websites</li>
        <li>Participate in cross-app tracking as defined by Apple's App Tracking Transparency framework</li>
        <li>Request access to the advertising identifier (IDFA)</li>
        <li>Display third-party advertising</li>
        <li>Share data with advertising networks</li>
        <li>Sell personal information</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not use data for behavioral advertising or advertising measurement.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2>4. How We Use Information</h2>
      <p>We use collected data to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Operate and maintain the app and platform</li>
        <li>Enable core functionality</li>
        <li>Monitor performance and uptime</li>
        <li>Prevent fraud and abuse</li>
        <li>Diagnose and fix errors</li>
        <li>Improve product stability and scalability</li>
        <li>Respond to website inquiries</li>
      </ul>

      <hr />

      <h2>5. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>We share data only with service providers necessary to operate the service:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Microsoft Azure</strong> — Application Insights diagnostics</li>
        <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — Hosting and security services</li>
        <li><strong>Google</strong> — Website analytics only</li>
        <li><strong>Resend</strong> — Transactional email for demo requests</li>
      </ul>
      <p>These providers process data on our behalf and are required to safeguard it. We do not share data with data brokers.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>We retain data only as long as necessary to maintain system reliability, investigate crashes and performance issues, and comply with legal obligations. Diagnostic data retention follows configured cloud provider retention policies.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2>7. Data Security</h2>
      <p>We implement industry-standard safeguards including HTTPS encryption in transit, cloud-based infrastructure security controls, restricted administrative access, and secure secret management practices.</p>
      <p>No system can guarantee absolute security, but we take reasonable steps to protect data.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2>8. Sensitive Information</h2>
      <p>Rally Trivia does not intentionally collect financial account information, government-issued identification numbers, health information, biometric identifiers, precise location data, or contact lists.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>Rally Trivia is designed for nonprofit organizations and corporate event planners and is not directed to children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child under 13 has provided personal information, please contact us at <a href="mailto:privacy@rallytrivia.com">privacy@rallytrivia.com</a> and we will promptly delete it.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2>10. International Users</h2>
      <p>Our services may be hosted in the United States and other jurisdictions where our service providers operate. By using Rally Trivia, you consent to such processing.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2>11. Your Privacy Rights</h2>
      <p>Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the right to access personal data, request correction, request deletion, restrict processing, or object to processing.</p>
      <p>Because the app does not collect personally identifiable user accounts, most mobile app usage data cannot be directly tied to an individual.</p>
      <p>For privacy inquiries or deletion requests, contact: <a href="mailto:privacy@rallytrivia.com">privacy@rallytrivia.com</a></p>

      <hr />

      <h2>12. California Privacy Rights (CCPA)</h2>
      <p>If you are a California resident, you have the right to know what personal information we collect and how it is used, request deletion of your personal information, opt out of the sale of personal information (we do not sell personal information), and not be discriminated against for exercising your privacy rights.</p>
      <p>To exercise these rights, contact <a href="mailto:privacy@rallytrivia.com">privacy@rallytrivia.com</a>.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2>13. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will update the "Last Updated" date above. Continued use of Rally Trivia constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.</p>

      <hr />

      <h2>14. Contact Information</h2>
      <p>
        Rally Trivia<br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@rallytrivia.com">privacy@rallytrivia.com</a><br />
        Website: <a href="https://www.rallytrivia.com">https://www.rallytrivia.com</a>
      </p>

    </article>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
